<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="79" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1266,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1410,1436]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Externally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Volynkin &amp; Fan &amp; Wang, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Volynkin &amp; Fan &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[462,578,1411,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qinxiae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[462,578,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. qinxiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[587,653,1411,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[587,653,1411,1437]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is unique amongst the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1854" box="[999,1086,1411,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[999,1086,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Barsine</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the bicolored forewing with a scarlet ground color and a large black central patch. Since the female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Volynkin &amp; Fan &amp; Wang, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Volynkin &amp; Fan &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1033,1145,1447,1472]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qinxiae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1033,1145,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. qinxiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1153,1216,1447,1473]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1153,1216,1447,1473]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and the males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reich" authorityYear="1937" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Miltochrista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoenei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. hoenei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Volynkin &amp; Fan &amp; Wang, 2022" authorityName="Huang &amp; Volynkin &amp; Fan &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[280,402,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jingkuni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[280,402,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. jingkuni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[409,472,1483,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[409,472,1483,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are unknown, the copulatory organ of the new species is compared only to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mell" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1313,1436,1483,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardalis">
<emphasis box="[1313,1436,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. pardalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,276,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,193,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-25@5.[155,1432,181,1867]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Adults of Barsine spp. Depositories of the specimens: 9, 10 in MfN; 11 in SCAU; 12–16 in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796815/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[289,319,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,190,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[155,1432,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Male genitalia of Barsine spp. Depositories of the slides: 17 in SCAU; 18 in CHSY; 19 in MfN; 20 in MWM/ ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796819/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[332,405,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–27" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,187,1547]" captionTargetId="figure-25@7.[161,1427,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21–27. Female genitalia of Barsine spp. Depositories of the slides: 21 in SCAU; 22 in CHSY; 23 in MfN; 24 in the private collection of Yasunori Kishida; 25 in ZFMK; 26, 27 in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796821/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">23, 24</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[470,585,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseata">
<emphasis box="[470,585,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. roseata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[601,731,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1891,1915]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,193,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-25@5.[155,1432,181,1867]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Adults of Barsine spp. Depositories of the specimens: 9, 10 in MfN; 11 in SCAU; 12–16 in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796815" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796815/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Figs 11–16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[743,774,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,190,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[155,1432,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Male genitalia of Barsine spp. Depositories of the slides: 17 in SCAU; 18 in CHSY; 19 in MfN; 20 in MWM/ ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796819/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[786,817,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–27" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,187,1547]" captionTargetId="figure-25@7.[161,1427,181,1560]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 21–27. Female genitalia of Barsine spp. Depositories of the slides: 21 in SCAU; 22 in CHSY; 23 in MfN; 24 in the private collection of Yasunori Kishida; 25 in ZFMK; 26, 27 in MWM/ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796821" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796821/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">27</figureCitation>
), from which it is distinguished by the combination of the following characters. (1) The uncus is shorter. (2) The membranous lobe of the valva is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mell" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[1312,1436,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardalis">
<emphasis box="[1312,1436,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. pardalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but shorter and narrower than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[527,643,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseata">
<emphasis box="[527,643,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. roseata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (3) The basal saccular process is thick and short while it is long and slender in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[267,381,1627,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseata">
<emphasis box="[267,381,1627,1652]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. roseata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mell" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[434,557,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardalis">
<emphasis box="[434,557,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. pardalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (4) The dorsal lobe of the distal saccular process is long and thumb-like while it is vestigial in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1864" box="[332,455,1663,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseata">
<emphasis box="[332,455,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. roseata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and short and dent-like in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mell" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[758,882,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardalis">
<emphasis box="[758,882,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">B. pardalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (5) The phallus is much longer and slender than in the congeners. (6) The 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[448,459,1699,1713]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">st</superScript>
medial diverticulum of the vesica is markedly smaller, shorter and narrower. (7) The 2 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1420,1436,1698,1712]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">nd</superScript>
medial diverticulum is conspicuously smaller, narrower and scattered with larger cornuti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1266,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,1770,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[430,533,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,189,1730]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1437,181,1739]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Adults of Barsine spp. Depositories of the specimens: 1, 3 in SCAU; 2, 4–6 in CHSY; 7 in ZFMK; 8 in MWM/ ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796813/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 15.5–17.2 mm (n=2, 17. 
<quantity box="[1024,1092,1771,1797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in 
<typeStatus box="[1131,1234,1771,1797]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">holotype</typeStatus>
). Antenna weakly ciliate. Head and thorax covered with scarlet hair-like scales. Abdomen covered with hair-like scales, black dorsally and scarlet ventrally. Forewing ground color scarlet with large black oval central patch. An additional black lengthwise stripe present at dorsum. Cilia scarlet. Hindwing ground color black. Cilia black above anal angle and reddish at anal angle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1266,2013]" box="[199,401,1951,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1266,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="80" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,387,1986,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Genitalia. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[403,537,1987,2013]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–20" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1845,1869]" captionTargetBox="[165,1423,190,1807]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[155,1432,181,1821]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–20. Male genitalia of Barsine spp. Depositories of the slides: 17 in SCAU; 18 in CHSY; 19 in MfN; 20 in MWM/ ZSM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796819" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6796819/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="79">Figs 17, 18</figureCitation>
). Uncus short and curved subapically. Tegumen triangular, relatively short and broad. Juxta broad, X-shaped. Saccus broad, U-shaped. Valva lobular. Costa heavily sclerotized, medial costal process broadly triangular. Membranous lobe of valva narrow and short. Sacculus heavily sclerotized, with thick and stout basal process. Distal lobe of distal saccular process long and narrow, distally somewhat tapered and apically rounded. Dorsal lobe of distal saccular process slightly shorter than distal one, gradually tapered distally and gently curved medially. Phallus slender, tubular and almost straight. Vesica broad with short basal diverticulum. 1 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1425,1436,295,309]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">st</superScript>
medial diverticulum of vesica long and broad, with granulation field distally. 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1024,1040,330,344]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">nd</superScript>
medial diverticulum short, covered with numerous cornuti of different sizes from base to subapical section. 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[981,995,366,380]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">rd</superScript>
medial diverticulum broad basally and abruptly narrowed towards distal end, covered with large cornuti basally and granulation field in the elongated part. 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[165,178,438,452]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">th</superScript>
medial diverticulum vestigial. 5 
<superScript attach="left" box="[541,554,438,452]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">th</superScript>
medial diverticulum globular, covered with numerous cornuti of various sizes. Basal plate of vesica ejaculatorius long and broad, triangular.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1083,510,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="80" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,1083,510,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,510,536]" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">Distribution.</emphasis>
Currently only known from 
<collectingRegion box="[675,882,511,537]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">Zhejiang Province</collectingRegion>
in Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1008,1079,511,537]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="80" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Ms. Qin-xi Xie, the beloved of the collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[1221,1322,547,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="80">holotype</typeStatus>
, Mr. Jingkun Zhang.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
